,\"pauvreté\"]', 'This study focuses on “Humanitarian Action in Chad: World Vision Intervention in the \nWestern Logon region (1985-2022)”. It aims to highlight the humanitarian contribution of the \nWorld Vision Organization in the Western Logon region. A region strongly affected and \nimpoverished by the various crises that affected Chad in general. This work, which extends over \nfour chapters, has made it possible to establish the origins of the intervention of this \nOrganization in Western Logon. Subsequently, he focused on the action program developed by \nWorld Vision to improve the living conditions of the target population. The work shows that for \nalmost three decades, and despite the obstacles linked to its proper functioning, World Vision \nhas improved the living standards of vulnerable people. The Organization has invested in \nsetting up sustainable development projects focused on education and sponsorship of children, \nemergency humanitarian aid and reconstruction, awareness campaigns called \"advocacy \ncampaigns\", support and nutritional care for vulnerable people and the fight against major \nepidemics. To carry out our work, we conducted field surveys to collect oral testimonies related \nto this subject. The written documents present in different documentations centers and on the \nInternet were also used and analyzed using a qualitative and qualitative approach. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, '2025-09-25 20:21:51', '2025-09-26 03:57:29', 0, 1, '300', NULL, '[]', NULL, NULL, 'MEM2025002', 'CAMES-CM-UDM-2025-ME-002', 'UDM-2025-ME-002', '123456789/udm-2025-me-002', 'available', 'graduate', 'print', 'fr', NULL, 0);

