défis de gestion des \nprésences académiques, offrant à la fois un suivi en temps réel et une interface intuitive pour \nles utilisateurs et les administrateurs. Elle incarne un pas important vers la modernisation des \nprocessus administratifs et le renforcement de la sécurité au sein des institutions d\'enseignement \nsupérieur.', 'In an era where digital transformation has become imperative for academic institutions, \nmanaging attendance remains a significant challenge, often hindered by manual methods that \nare prone to errors and fraud. This project proposes an innovative solution for the University of \nMontagnes, aiming to automate and secure staff attendance tracking through a mobile \napplication. This solution leverages QR codes, biometric technology (fingerprint and facial \nrecognition), and geolocation validation. \nThe multiplatform application allows users to register their attendance by scanning QR codes \nat various strategic points across the campus, while simultaneously verifying their identity and \nlocation in real-time. A dedicated web interface enables administrators to manage users, \ngenerate reports, and oversee centralized and secure attendance data. \nTo ensure flexibility, security, and scalability, the project relies on technologies such as NestJS \nfor the backend, Ionic for mobile development, and MySQL for data management. This \napproach provides simplified, accurate attendance management that meets the institution\'s \nrequirements while enhancing the protection of personal and biometric data. \nIn conclusion, this application offers an innovative response to the challenges of academic \nattendance management, providing both real-time tracking and an intuitive interface for users \nand administrators. It represents a significant step towards modernizing administrative \nprocesses and strengthening security within higher education institutions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '[\"UdM\",\"presence\",\"conception\"]', 'rapport_stage/ba1b47ec-3f